---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import CapitalGainsTaxCalculator from "../../../components/CapitalGainsTaxCalculator.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Capital Gains Tax Calculator (Canada) | CRA Inclusion Rates"
  description="Estimate your Canadian capital gains tax. Understand how the 50% inclusion rate affects your taxable income and marginal tax rate."
>
  <main class="flex-grow pt-24 pb-20">
    <!-- Title Section -->
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 mb-8 text-center sm:text-left">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-white tracking-tight font-sans">
        Capital Gains Tax Calculator (Canada)
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 mt-2 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        Model your potential CRA tax liability using the standard 50% inclusion rate for Canadian residents.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Calculator Component -->
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <CapitalGainsTaxCalculator defaultCountry="CA" />
    </div>

    <!-- Explainer Content -->
    <div class="border-t border-slate-800/60 mt-12 bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-950 to-slate-950/95">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-16 px-4">
        <section>
          <div class="mb-6">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-400 border border-emerald-500/20 mb-4">Tax Strategy (Canada)</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-extrabold text-white tracking-tight leading-snug">
              Understanding Canadian Capital Gains Tax
            </h2>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-8 text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
            <article>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-3">Introduction</h3>
              <p>
                In Canada, you do not pay tax on the entire profit you make from selling an asset. Instead, only a portion of the gain is included in your taxable income. This calculator estimates your liability using the CRA inclusion rate.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-2">
                For a comprehensive guide on minimizing these taxes, check out our <a href="/blog/capital-gains-tax-canada/" class="text-[#00F5D4] hover:underline">Canadian Capital Gains Tax Guide</a>.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-3">Key Concepts</h3>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                <li><strong>Inclusion Rate:</strong> Currently, the standard inclusion rate is 50%. This means only half of your capital gain is taxable.</li>
                <li><strong>Marginal Tax Rates:</strong> The taxable portion of your gain is added to your other income for the year and taxed at your marginal federal and provincial tax rates.</li>
                <li><strong>Capital Losses:</strong> Capital losses can only be used to offset capital gains, not ordinary income. They can be carried back 3 years or carried forward indefinitely.</li>
              </ul>
            </article>
            
            <article>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-3">Methodology</h3>
              <p>
                The calculator calculates your total gain by subtracting the purchase price from the sale amount. It then applies the 50% inclusion rate to find your taxable capital gain. Finally, it estimates the tax owed based on a blended marginal rate calculated from your other income.
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 italic mt-4">
                Source: <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/revenue-agency/services/tax/individuals/topics/about-your-tax-return/tax-return/completing-a-tax-return/personal-income/line-12700-capital-gains.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="hover:text-slate-300 underline">CRA - Line 12700 Capital Gains</a>.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>

          <!-- FAQ Accordion -->
          <div class="mt-12 border-t border-slate-800/80 pt-10">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest bg-amber-500/10 text-amber-400 border border-amber-500/20 mb-4">FAQ</span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>

            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="border border-slate-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden bg-slate-900/50">
                <button class="w-full flex items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 text-left group cursor-pointer" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('hidden'); this.querySelector('svg').classList.toggle('rotate-180');">
                  <span class="font-semibold text-white">What is the capital gains inclusion rate in Canada?</span>
                  <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-slate-500 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
                </button>
                <div class="hidden px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-slate-400">
                  Currently, the inclusion rate is 50%, meaning only half of your total capital gain is subject to tax at your marginal rate. Note that recent proposals may change this for gains over $250,000.
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="border border-slate-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden bg-slate-900/50">
                <button class="w-full flex items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 text-left group cursor-pointer" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('hidden'); this.querySelector('svg').classList.toggle('rotate-180');">
                  <span class="font-semibold text-white">How does my other income affect capital gains tax?</span>
                  <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-slate-500 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
                </button>
                <div class="hidden px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-slate-400">
                  Since the taxable portion of your capital gain is added to your other income, a higher regular income will push the gain into a higher marginal tax bracket, increasing the tax owed on the gain.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Internal Links -->
          <div class="mt-12 border-t border-slate-800/80 pt-10">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Related Calculators</h3>
            <div class="flex flex-col space-y-2">
              <a href="/tax-loss-harvesting-calculator/canada/" class="text-[#00F5D4] hover:underline">Canadian Tax Loss Harvesting Calculator</a>
              <a href="/buy-borrow-die-calculator/canada/" class="text-[#00F5D4] hover:underline">Buy, Borrow, Die Strategy Calculator (Canada)</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <script type="application/ld+json" slot="head">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much is the capital gains tax in Canada?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Canada does not have a specific 'capital gains tax rate'. Instead, 50% of your capital gain is included in your income and taxed at your marginal tax rate."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the capital gains inclusion rate?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "The inclusion rate determines what portion of a capital gain is taxable. The standard rate is 50%, meaning half the profit is tax-free."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  </script>
</Layout>
